Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane doesn't believe former President Jacob Zuma should spend time behind bars. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Public Protector Busisiwe Mkhwebane believes former President Jacob Zuma should not be sent to jail. Mkhwebane says she aligns herself with the Constitutional Court's minority judgment. She was responding to questions during a briefing on Wednesday. READ: Zuma in 'high spirits' despite jail sentence: spokesperson On Tuesday, the apex court sentenced Zuma to 15 months imprisonment for contempt of court. The minority judgment held that the former president should be given a suspended sentence.